abstract: Commerce Dept reports home sales fell 0.2 percent in January to seasonally adjusted annual rate of 481,000 units, and that December's sales pace was revised to 482,000 from 481,000.
lead_paragraph: The Commerce Department reported that new single-family home sales fell in January, but, in a hopeful sign, supply and prices both rose.

headline.main: Sales of New Homes Dip, but Other Signals Are Strong
